- Operator 0 refers to the default operator in the system, possibly an automated system or admin; 
- Temperature parameter is crucial for experiment environment control; 
- Access count more than 5 implies the experiment has been actively used or observed.

; 
; The cumulative cost refers to the total cost incurred by an experiment up to a certain point in time, calculated by summing up the costs of all sessions in the experiment, ordered by the session start time.
; The total measurements refer to the total number of measurements taken in an experiment.
